article_title: 'Irresponsible': White House official calls out western media for missing facts
meta_description:
A White House official took to Twitter to call out western media for not mentioning an important point while quoting CDC’s warning about the Delta variant of coronavirus.

In an internal paper, the US Centers for Sickness Control and Prevention (CDC) warned that the Delta variant of coronavirus can be passed on even by vaccinated people and may even be deadlier than previous strains of COVID-19.

article_title: Doctors study severity of Delta strain amid concerns over transmission
meta_description: Research in Canada, Singapore and Scotland shows people, mainly those who are unvaccinated, infected with Delta variant are more likely to be hospitalised than patients earlier during the pandemic.

article_title: Jabs Forever: UK to Offer 32 Million 'Booster' Vaccines Next Month
meta_description: The British government will reportedly begin rolling out 32 million "booster" vaccines by next month to all those over the age of 50.

article_title: Coronavirus Updates: US employers ratchet up the pressure on the unvaccinated
meta_description: Employers are increasingly losing patience with unvaccinated workers who refuse to get the COVID-19 shot.

article_title: Combining AstraZeneca and mRNA COVID-19 vaccines is effective -Danish study
meta_description: Combining AstraZeneca's (AZN.L) COVID-19 vaccine with a second dose from either Pfizer-BioNTech (PFE.N), (22UAy.DE) or Moderna's (MRNA.O) jab provides "good protection", Denmark's State Serum Institute said on Monday.
